ENTRY            F0639   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0639001   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 11         22
TITLE      Investigation of large angle structure in alpha-
           scattering from calcium isotopes between Ea = 36-61 MeV
AUTHOR     (H.Lohner,H.Eickhoff,D.Frekers,G.Gaul,K.Poppensieker,
           R.Santo,A.G.Drentje,L.W.Put)
INSTITUTE  (2GERMST,2NEDKVI)
REFERENCE  (J,ZP/A,286,99,1978)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2NEDKVI) Variable energy cyclotron of the KVI
INC-SOURCE Non-analyzed alpha-particle beam (delta E / E = 0.003)
DETECTOR   (SIBAR) Six surface barrier detectors with angular
           distance of 8 degrees were mounted on a rotatable ring.
METHOD     (EDE)
SAMPLE     Self-supporting metallic Ca-foils [natural Ca and
           enriched 44Ca (98.6%)] with thickness between
           800 ug/cm2 and 1500 ug/cm2 were used as targets.
ERR-ANALYS The statistical errors of the elastic scattering data
           are on the average less than 5% except for cross
           sections lower than 10 ub/sr when the uncertainties
           rise up to 20% for the higher energy. The overall
           energy resolution in the spectra was about 250 keV at
           forward angles and 350 keV at backward angles.
HISTORY    (20050614C)
           (20251217U) SD: Small corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              22
COMMON               2          3
ANG-RSL    ERR-DIG
ADEG       PER-CENT
        0.7        0.1
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           29
SUBENT        F0639002   20251217   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  3          3
REACTION   (20-CA-40(A,EL)20-CA-40,,DA,,RTH)
STATUS     (CURVE,,H.Lohner+,J,ZP/A,286,99,1978) Fig.2
HISTORY    (20251217U) SD: BIB updated.
ENDBIB               3
COMMON               1          3
ANG-ERR-D
ADEG
        0.8
ENDCOMMON            3
